                    <p>One day in late May, I decided that I would build a real-time map of all of the tweets in the UK and tokenize them individually in real-time using the Stanford Natural Language Parsing library. The Stanford Named Entity Recognizer (also known as the CRFClassifier in techie speak), processes strings of text, extracting the "named entities" of a sentence. These are the named people, places or organisations in a sentence.</p>
